<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-05-07T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-05-07T14:00:00-05:00" n="383" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">863.51 Relief Credits/362b:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Germany</hi>
                                        (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-05-07T15:00:00-04:00">May 7, 1938—3 p.m.</date></dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>62. Department’s 35, April 5, 7 p.m. What is pertinence of Berlin
                                    press despatches of May 3 reporting German decree prohibiting
                                    the transfer of service moneys respecting all Austrian
                                    loans?</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>